Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_oa_lib(25.10)                                      report_oa_lib(25.10)

Name
       report_oa_lib  -  Reports  information  about OpenAccess libraries from
       within Innovus

Syntax
       report_oa_lib

       [-help]

       <lib_name>

       [-header]

       [-filter {cdsinfo  |  compression  |  constraint_groups  |  property  |
       tech_graph}]

       Reports information about OpenAccess libraries from within Innovus. You
       can  use  this  command  to query for attributes that are controlled by
       some of the setOaxMode options and the update_oa_lib command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each report_oa_lib parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man report_oa_lib.

       -filter {cdsinfo | compression | constraint_groups | property |
       tech_graph}
              Specifies  the list of information to be included in the report.
              You can choose from the following filter options:

              * cdsinfo - Reports whether the cdsinfo.tag exists in the speci-
                fied library.

              * compression - Reports the compression level (0 = uncompressed)
                of the library.

              * constraint_groups - Reports the constraint groups  defined  in
                the  libraries in the technology graph. Constraint groups that
                are compatible with the default rule  and  NONDEFAULTRULE  re-
                quirements will be indicated.

              * property  - Reports the property information that was added to
                the library. The add_oa_library_property command is one source
                of library properties.

              * tech_graph - Reports information about  the  technology  graph
                from the specified library.

              If you do not specify a filter option, all the above information
              is included in the report.

       -header
              Indicates  that header information should be displayed. This op-
              tion is useful if the report is being redirected to a file.

       <lib_name>
              Specifies the name of the OpenAccess library to be queried.

Example
       The following command reports information about the  zambezi45  OpenAc-
       cess library along with the header:

       innovus 18> report_oa_lib zambezi45 -header

       ;********************************

       ; Header Info

